          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Border Enforcement, Security, And Funding Enhancement Act or the BE SAFE Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires each alien granted lawful permanent residence to pay a $2,500 fee before receiving a Permanent Resident Card (commonly referred to as the &quot;Green Card&quot;), in addition to any other required fees. The collected funds shall go into the newly established Border Security Enhancement Fund, and may be used to enforce immigration laws and improve immigration-related processes, including (1) constructing border barriers, (2) carrying out enforcement and removal operations, (3) improving infrastructure at border crossings, and (4) verifying the status of student visa holders.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2019-03-04</actionDate>
